reviews.text: When in Madison... The terrace is a great place to visit, have a beer, get some lunch, just hang out. I think you're supposed to somehow be affiliated with the University, but an annual membership is pretty  inexpensive and it's the perfect place to gather, especially when the weather is nice and you can sit outside by the lake.

The winter carnival and the "liberty statue head." Was attended by many including children but the weather wasn't great this year. A great event to attend no matter what the weather. Activities for all ages.
One word... Terrace! This place is great year around but summer time sitting on the terrace and looking out at Lake Mendota, is epic!

So much nostalgia. 
I graduated from UW in 2003 and have been back a few times since my move down south. I never miss a trip to the Terrace. 
Our last trip it was cold so we didn't spend too much time outside on those iconic chairs but we did enjoy walking around inside. I was surprised to see how many restaurants have opened up in there and I was a bit disappointed by how commercial they felt but you can't stop progress! 
The ice cream there is amazingly good and a pitcher of beer on the Terrace in the warmer months is perfect.
Good fun whatever the weather. Got to standing on a frozen lake here in winter and in summer it's a great place to have a drink and hang out!

We took my two year old. He hasn't really had much exposure to real public things. He loved it without a doubt. Spacious place that can be easily mapped out for a smoke break half way through. The other guest were very polite and courteous We look forward to coming back

Great place to take your kids to see some cool animals. And for being a free zoo, it has a lot to offer. The carousel and the train ride are always fun for the kids and the park inside the zoo is rather large as well. There is also a picnic area inside as well as a restaurant to eat at if you choose that looks out at some of the exhibits. Definitely a great and affordable option for fun with the family.

The Henry Vilas Zoo here in Madison is a little treasure although small and free it still offers a wide variety of species of animals to view in safe for the public and safe for the animals compounds. It also has a great children's zoo with many interesting things for children to do while also learning about the animalswithin it. The park that is part of the zoo is great for outdoor activities including picnics. There is a bike path through the area and small beach that is part of the area. The zoo is a wonderful way to spend an afternoon with the family you can bring your own food and drinks and use the picnic tables here or you can get food from one of the many food outlets in the zoo. You owe it to yourself and your family to come and see the Henry Vilas Zoo in Madison, Wisconsin.

I love zoos. But this one was sad. The enclosures were dirty and terribly small. I understand not all zoos are going to be able to have large natural habitats for each animal...but provide for the few animals they do have(the giraffe, lion and tiger areas are so small the have no room to run or burn off energy) . Clean areas, enough space for the animals to run and exercise, fresh water...
This zoo could be really nice, a great place for families if they could clean it up and provide for the animals they have(and get the trash out of the cages).

Excellent free zoo. Plenty of outdoor and indoor exhibits to explore. A cafe is on site if you get hungry. Great place to see primates, lions, tigers, bears and my favorite the red pandas. My family and I love going here. Afterward you can take a walk through the adjoining park or swim in the lake.

Great variety of habitat types to walk through, native prairie and woods. My favorite part is the open part where tree species are labeled. Great both summer and winter. Beware in the spring for the mud!
One of my favorite places in Madison to get a trail run in. Some great single track trails and open trails

Heaven in the middle of a city! If you can concentrate on the sounds, smells and beauty of the gardens you might be able to not hear the hum of the Beltline. Go deeper into the trails, you will definitely not hear the Beltline and find heaven in the middle of a city. Spring and Fall are a must for smells and photos. If you need to get away, but can't. Take a trail, for 45 minutes. Honestly, heaven!

We saw a huge and gorgeous turkey cross the road right in front of us about 10 feet away, it was absolutely beautiful, and this is in mid March! Great for birdwatching, we saw an enormous pileated woodpecker making a tremendous amount of noise pecking at a giant tree, we saw nuthatches and mallards, deer tracks. I imagine this place would be fantastic for animal watching in summertime. The spring that bubbles up from underneath   a big tree is worth seeing, as I like all forms of water features, and it interests me to see water come up out of the ground, as if by magic. Lots of people walking, jogging, hiking, and biking even though it was about 45 degrees outside. The Visitor Center is very pleasant, the desk person super informative and helpful. It's worth giving them a few dollars in donation to keep up the trails and such, seeing as how there is no fee to get in.
Love to walk around the Arboretum during any season.
A nice, quiet, informative look into the history of Wyoming. Really pretty fascinating to see the layout. I think my favorite room was the Sun Porch on the 2nd floor.
My husband and I loved going to this house and it’s free!! Employees are very kind and friendly. You should definitely go!!
This place was a hidden gem. Free entry & really neat to see.

Came in there almost at 5pm while passing through Cheyenne. Nevertheless the local museum workers were happy to let us in and even gave us a short tour -- all for free. Really nice and somewhat educational place to visit with a family.
Amazing place! There are so many cool details.  I'd have to say my favorite part was the music box by the stairs.

Madison's No. 1 for world-quality contemporary art exhibitions. A beautiful space complimented by an intelligent, informed staff. Every visit to this Madison treasure is an awakening inspiration to art & life.

Very beautiful as well as friendly staff. There was no fee for admission. They did have Foods set up to receive donations. They had only two galleries available to see that were open. They are renovating and getting ready to open the rest within a month. Can't wait to go back and see the rest! It was very clean and I felt very comfortable and relaxed while viewing all of the art. They even had a tablet with a video showing one of the artists conception from the very beginning of his process all the way to a piece of completed work.
Admittedly, I’m biased since I work for the museum. But I was a fan even before that. Great exhibitions, education stations, a rooftop sculpture garden with gorgeous views, and free admission!
Shopped in the gift shop.  Amazing inventory... I love artful items that reflect individuality and creativity.  Nice textiles, jewelry, glass,...
Nice place to take the kids on a rainy, wet day. Enjoyed the art on display as well.

The Children's museum is pretty awesome for families with kids from about 2-8 plus or minus. Many activities to keep the kids entertained and curious for hours. One visit won't be enough. Best to get the membership and visit a lot. Patrons are mostly a considerate and respectful bunch. Highly recommended.

Pretty great museum. It's better when the weather is nice so there is a little bit more to do. It does get very hot in the building, but there's a lot of energy and bodies so that is to be expected. Lots of fun.

This place is really awesome. I'd read that there was a lot for 3- to 5-year-olds to do, but I also thought my one-year-old had a ton of fun, especially in the little water garden. I do think being able to stand and crawl is pretty important in order to make the most of the museum,  but just watching all the other kids play would be a lot of fun for most infants.

Also, if you are a first- time parent, you (and a second adult) get a free membership until baby is 18 mo!

Fun place, not huge, but lots to do.  Best suited for 4-6 year olds in my opinion.  My daughter likes the playground and the outdoor roof space the best.  Their craft area is full of items for free creating.

The place seemed small for the price we paid. It was extremely crowded which did not help the experience.  My 4 year old enjoyed most of it, my 1 year old did not find a whole she could do. The staff was great with the kids and had some neat programs.

Madison's No. 1 for world-quality contemporary art exhibitions. A beautiful space complimented by an intelligent, informed staff. Every visit to this Madison treasure is an awakening inspiration to art & life.

Very beautiful as well as friendly staff. There was no fee for admission. They did have Foods set up to receive donations. They had only two galleries available to see that were open. They are renovating and getting ready to open the rest within a month. Can't wait to go back and see the rest! It was very clean and I felt very comfortable and relaxed while viewing all of the art. They even had a tablet with a video showing one of the artists conception from the very beginning of his process all the way to a piece of completed work.
Admittedly, I’m biased since I work for the museum. But I was a fan even before that. Great exhibitions, education stations, a rooftop sculpture garden with gorgeous views, and free admission!
Shopped in the gift shop.  Amazing inventory... I love artful items that reflect individuality and creativity.  Nice textiles, jewelry, glass,...
Nice place to take the kids on a rainy, wet day. Enjoyed the art on display as well.

You have to try the Pad Lao. It's amazing. Similar to Pad Thai, but different enough to be really interesting, and I haven't seen it offered anywhere else. Carry out is fast and easy, and I've never seen the dining room full. I love this place.
Great authentic Asian food, some of the best we've had! The portion sizes were huge and the waitress was super nice. Definitely going to come back again. Tasted just like home 😁

I've only ever eaten two things here, Singapore Noodles (medium spice) and fresh spring rolls. I've been eating these two dishes here for over a decade, and have never had them be anything  but delicious.  It's cozy and the service is quick.  If you're just looking for decor and hip ambiance, go elsewhere.

This place set the standard for spicy curry dishes in Madison, but those days are past. Recent curry orders have been mostly onions and potatoes with a small amount of tough, unappealing beef. Vientiane was so good 20 years ago, but after a couple of recent orders  we realize that it's just not worth it. Food is too expensive and not that good. Delivery is too expensive with the multiple charges (just like everywhere else). Uber and EatStreet are making money while we pay more for smaller portions. Just get carryout from Ha Long Bay instead.

I don't usually give reviews - and never leave bad reviews, but this place is an exception.  Since the place had 4 stars, I picked it over others.

The food was the worst Asian food I have ever had.  I ordered the coconut soup - it was mostly onions and what chicken was in the soup was gristle/scraps.  

I also had the Pad Thai.  The noodles were mush.  Total mush.  Have you ever had overcooked macaroni and cheese that has zero texture?  That is exactly what the texture was - but with long noodles with Pad Thai flavoring in it.
Love this place!  Good food,  good ambiance, good prices. State Street aty is best. Do go and enjoy!
Really friendly hosts, and the food is unmatched! Best falafel sandwich spot in town.

The best international place on campus, on State Street Madison besides US Madison campus itself. U got the warmth, u can speak Spanish, French, Arabic, English in there, the music too is eclectic... Talk with the owner, Faycal, that's the best human being around.  Been coming here since 2004, I always come back...after traveling the world...yep it is that good. And yes, I studied here all the way to get my Doctorate as you can see, the owner is not just a friend, he became my family and I couldn't have done this without his friendship.
Music is amazing, people are warm, and there's very delicious food!
My boyfriend and I eat here almost every Saturday. We love the shawarma and the algerian tea. Just make sure to note their hours as they're somewhat limited and make sure to bring cash.
I've heard about this place for years.  It's way better than they say it is.  Great food and awesome staff.  Maya was great!  It's a Madison tradition worth experiencing.  I can't wait to go back!
I love this spot. If you can handle the college crowd and paying cash then you're in for a treat. This place has some of the best tasting breakfast food in the downtown Madison area!

The best place for breakfast/brunch in Madison!

The scrambler is amazing! Always order extra gravy with them!( Portions are huge)

Heads up- Mickies Dairy Bar is cash only, but they do have an ATM inside ! 

The staff are all very friendly and genuinely look like they enjoy working there!

Charm, nostalgia, affordability, hospitality, this place has it all. The staff is so sweet, the food is so delicious, the prices are so reasonable, and this place is dripping with sentimentality. Love the cozy layout and 1950s decor and efficiency. We'll definitely be back to enjoy more of their delicious diner fair.

The diner to go to in Madison. Just avoid the weekends unless you want one hell of a wait! Their food on a Wednesday morning is just as good and a lot less stressful. Cash only but they have a super cheap atm.

I had the most amazing experience at brunch today!! I hosted a party of 30 for a going away party and it was AWESOME!!  The staff were SO attentive and totally spot on! I know the they were waiting us and other tables, but we would have never noticed!! They were always right there and catered to our EVERY NEED!!!  I was so stressed hosting up until we got there. Once we arrived, EVERYTHING was taken care of! I never lifted a finger, it was magic! Also, the food was awesome and the ginormous list of bloody marys was to die for!! Even the management were a regular visit, just to make sure we were all taken care of. So impressed by the integrity of the staff and food. I really cannot say enough about this place to do it justice!! And I cannot say enough about the friendly staff!! They were all smiles the whole time and had fun with us, just awesome! Exactly what I wanted to send a dear friend off to her new adventure. Awesome, awesome, AWESOME!!!

Always good food no matter when I have gone to eat here.  A mix of modern cuisine coupled with classics.
i would recommend to anyone who goes here needs to try the Cookie Dough Egg-Roll
Really good breakfast options, food and drinks alike. Prices are reasonable, but don't expect enough for leftovers. Probably worth making a reservation, if you're doing brunch.

I ordered the Chicken Schnitzel due to the description on the menu, which was amazing.  However, the entire dish was sitting in a small pool of oil, and it all tasted like Broccoli.  The Spaetzle with it was thick and not done well at all.  Overall would not recommend that dish, but the restaurant atmosphere itself wasn't bad at all.  Also the dessert is phenomenal, but the dinner was sadly lacking.

Had a Pee Wee chicken and noodles with crispy vegetables.  Not impressed.  Noodles were swimming in sauce, and barely any vegies. It's perfect for someone who likes noodles with their sauce only. Would not order it again. Not fit for the price. Hostess was not too pleasant either, for no apparent reason. Other staff was a little better, however, when we ordered unlimited bread and butter, took forever to get the second coming of the order, and had to finally ask a different waitress to bring it out. They only brought two orders of bread, not really unlimited.  Waitress didn't even come back to check on us or apologize about forgetting to bring the bread...just seemed not to remember at all that we paid to order an unlimited item from their menu. We paid for our meal and stayed for a little while longer to chat, and no one came to check on us for our coffee refills, and even when they were flagged down and we asked for refills, they still forgot to return to bring it. Perhaps just a bad day to stop in there, however we will definitely not plan to return.  They lost us as repeat customers.
Fun little place. Fairly small so get there early. Food is good if you like thin crust pizza. Pasta is good as well.
Fantastic Italian in an awesome vintage atmosphere. Downstairs, low ceiling, Christmas lights year-round. Full bar. Best thin-crust pizza in town.

I really enjoy the pesto..... simply delicious. I do wish the salads came with more olives though. I love the "tucked away" feel this place has and I think you will too.
Update11/8/18
They have a "reduced", smaller menu temporarily while they train replacement kitchen staff. They are NOT serving their Pesto dish.........yet.
Last night we had a delicious spinach and mushroom soup with pumpkin seeds and fall spices, a garden salad(no olives☹) and a thin crust pizza. It was all very good.
We had the pizza and some beers, the pizza is awesome, would definitely recommend.
The pizza is great and the ambiance is old school. Just watch your head if you're over six feet.

My wife and I ordered pizza as well as some lasagna from the one on Atwood on Saturday and all I can say is the pizza was burnt and lacked flavor and the lasagna was even worse. Zero flavor I mean it had no flavor just noodles with meat pretty much that’s it. I was told they had really good pizza but I can tell you that I will never buy pizza from them again. I’ve had bad pizza before but this ranks up there with some of the worst and we heard really good things about them but that cannot be anything recent. Sorry maybe you should focus on making some things really good instead of having a menu with so many items on it. The garlic toast it says is Texas toast however what we got is garlic bread you can buy from any store I know the taste because I buy it all the time. Shame on you there is no way it was Texas toast. I didn’t even bother to call back and tell them just going to chalk it up as experience and take my loss but for $31 dollars and change it was so not worth it save your money find someone who takes pride in their food they sell because you won’t find it there. Brian O

I order from here once in a while and had it delivered to my work. I’ve never had issues before with them. But the last time I ordered, I ordered the same thing I always do. I placed my order at 6:15, and my food did not arrive until almost 8. I understand that it gets busy at times so the initial time it took to revive my order is not what I am unhappy about. When it did arrive, half of my order was missing, and what I had received was cold. I then had to spend almost 20 minutes on the phone with them trying to explain that I had not received half of my food(the main part of my order). They gave me the option of taking a refund or having them remake my item. I told them if I didn’t want it, I would not have ordered it. Then it took another hour for them to bring me my remake. All in all, 3 hours after I ordered I received the rest of my food. I tried to contact them later to talk to somebody about my experience, and I have yet to hear back. Not thrilled. I will be taking my business elsewhere from now on.

Went in around 1am last night, expected the usual fare I’m used to from this fine establishment, but I was shocked and amazed by what I received. It was probably the best Thai pie I’ve ever had, and boy have I eaten a lot of Thai pies. My friend and I couldn’t stop making eye contact, smiling, and uttering the sole word of “pizza” to each other every slice. Not only was the pizza so good, but the woman running the bar (I wish I knew her name) was so friendly and helpful!

My salads I get from here is always juicy! I love the portions you get. Very delicious. But the way the workers handled me was very odd and kind of spooky! I knew what I was coming to order for days, once I came to place my order. I was treated like I was asking for too much and like they never seen a colored person before. But I took it as I was very beautiful that day! But glass nickels in general have good food 😇

Like to go here once in a while for a beer and a pizza with my wife. We're 3rd shift, so we can get a "lunch" from a place that stays open late and isn't chain diner food. Glad they have lots of options too so you're not shackled to pizza. Never had a bad meal here. The specialty pizzas are fun and tasty but don't be afraid to stray a bit on the menu. Thanks for being you, GNP.

This restaurant is by far my 
Favorite!! Everything I've ever eaten here has been Excellent!! I Can't Say Enough!! I Love the Vegan Food Here!!!! - Gary

I'm adding to this review, which I made about 7 months ago. Please see the above. The Green Owl just keeps getting better!! The employees there are first-rate!! The vegan food is Ambrosia!! There is No Better Restaurant in Madison!! I'd Give Them a Million Stars If I Could!! Vegans - This Place is Heaven!!

The food is divine. The menu is a dream if you’re vegetarian or vegan - so many fun options to choose from, and it’s been delicious every time. My favorite so far is the crabby cake po’boy. The service tends to be pretty slow, but I’m willing to wait for the great food.

The Green Owl has won awards as the finest vegetarian restaurant in the state of Wisconsin. Owner Jennie is charming and sets the tone for this establishment.  A huge selection of entrees. I got the nut loaf on my last visit and it was perfect.Always fun to sit outdoors at the tables on the bustling and eclectic Schenk's Corner. Try it out and you will be satisfied.
There was a very good selection of food. The staff were very nice and friendly. Everyone enjoyed their food. Overall it was a very good restaurant!

First time in Madison, was recommended to try this place by a fellow vegan friend. It was absolutely delicious and unique, and the decor inside is adorable! If only I could have a Green Owl near me in Chicago. Will definitely come back next time I'm in the area.

Compared to most restaurants, 5 stars.  Compared to other James Beard Award winning restaurants?  3, at best.  My meal was about 6 months after the 2012 James Beard for Best Chef Midwest was awarded to Tory Miller.   I have a fairly extensive culinary background, I made the trip to Madison specifically to eat at this location. The wine selections that came with our Prix Fixe menu ( Chefs Tasting Experience I believe it was called? ) was much better than the meal itself.  We went with the regular wine pairing and the "reserve" pairing.  The regular pairing was ok, but the reserve pairing was spectacular.  

The food itself wasn't very...inspired.  There were several courses, such as a stuffed pasta, that came out cooked just a bit wrong.  Nothing horrendous, just not perfect.  I think it was $125 for the menu, and $50(?) for the regular wine pairing and $100(?) for the reserve wine pairing at the time.  I just remember the cost of the wine pairing and the food costing about the same as the standard menu cost at The French Laundry when I was a stagier there.  

I'll go there again soon and update the review I left (3 stars) to see if things have been improved.

Located directly north across the street from the Capitol building in downtown Madison, WI, this very warm and updated space is extremely welcoming. Off to the side of L'Etoile is Graze, a smartly appointed and lively gastropub with a large full service bar. Excellent array of appetizers, including oysters on the half shell, a rainbow trout dip, and a seasoned pickle, just to name a few. Exciting and varied entrees such as a brisket, mussels, hot chicken & pickles, and my favorite, locally sourced lamb. Great drink menu. Selection of locally crafted beers. Very knowledgeable staff. Reservations recommended as this is a very popular spot after work and into the evening hours.

Dining here made for one of the best experiences of my life. We chose the 7 course dinner with the wine pairing. The food was perfect, our sommelier was funny and picked the best wines, and the environment was lovely. I can't wait to come back.

An amazing experience as usual! The food was amazing, but my girlfriend and I always share our meals, especially at a place like L'etoile, and when we told our waiter she split each course between the two of us, on separate plates. That's the kind of thing that sets L'etoile apart from other restaurants.

Who gives L'Etoile 1 star?  My goodness that's just silly.  This is probably the best restaurant in the state.  It's very expensive, of course, but in this instance, you get what you pay for.  Chef Tory is wonderful.

We had a marvelous time here on an evening dinner date. We ordered the spinach artichoke dip, the pan seared salmon, and the salted caramel tart. The bread served was delicious-slightly sweet with an excellent texture. The dip was wonderful, with the pita chips done to perfection. The salmon and veggies were great as well. The only minor complaint was the tart. It was just ice cream on a pastry with some strawberries. It was very sweet and while a nice end to the meal, nothing special. Our hostess was very kind and attentive. Would recommend!

Excellent, excellent, excellent! We thoroughly enjoyed our lunch at the Harvest Restaurant. The portions were generous, the food was fresh, and the service was great. Our server was prompt, professional, and ensured that our order came out as expected. We commented that we wish we had known about this restaurant earlier, as we would have come for a nice dinner for two. We highly recommend the Harvest Restaurant, even if you're not at Thanksgiving Point for the "attractions."

Visiting this place  for lunch was an experience with fantastic price to value. The food itself is good, the complimentary bread is delicious, the ambiance is amazing. Service was on point as well. The only downside was I felt a bit squished into the table at my booth seat, but that's getting pretty picky. If you're looking for a nice place for lunch or even a date, this is a good place to go. If you have a bunch of kids, it'll be too expensive.

This place has some good food, but the menu is lacking and a place with this high of prices and what appears to be semi-formal dress the items on the menu don't seem on par. Like I said, the food is good but meatloaf, Mac and cheese with pork belly  or chicken pot pie for  around $20.00? I think they could do better or take down prices a notch.

I'm not sure I actually want to post why I love going to the Harvest restaurant, but it's because everything   around the area is so busy and loud at lunch. I love to schedule lunch meetings here where we sit down quickly can have a quiet distraction free meeting. Of course the food is great and wonderful value. There's lots of great options you can't go wrong on what you order.

My friend and I are searching for a place to eat close by the Kohl Center, did a Google search and found The Tornado Steak House.  When we got there, first of all we were taken aback by the appearance of the outside of the restaurant (never judge a book by its cover). We were the first ones on shortly after 4:30, and wanted table (figuring we shouldn't have any problem getting a table) nope, they were booked until 7:30, and now know why.  So we ate at the bar.  All drinks made from scratch.  Not only did the bartenders know what they were doing, they were fun to watch (both ran that bar like a well oiled machine).  Then we got our food, not only piping hot, but absolutely delicious.  The steak was not only mouth watering, but it literally melted in your mouth.  If your looking for a great place for steak, this is one place I highly recommend. They also have a lot of other items to choose from... Rabbit, Duck, Venison, Salmon, just to name a few.  If the steaks are indicative of the rest of their food I know you'll enjoy eating there.  Prices are on the higher end of the spectrum, but absolutely worth every penny.

Never having been to this place, my friend and I really did not know what to expect when we ungracefully stumbled through those jankity metal doors on the street side of the building. However when we got inside we realized we were far under dressed in our casual clothes. It felt a little pretentious in there with all the business suits and argyle sweater vests but we were able to find a seat in the bar and we were served wonderfully. It just has a feel of "hole in the wall bar" but then is filled with high class people. The food was incredible and came out quickly despite how busy they were. Menu is a little limited and with high prices for just about everything besides the appetizers.

Great experience, excellent service! The food was fantastic worth the cost!  Bar seating was a perfect set up for a cozy drink before the meal. Adam our server recommend the perfect cocktail.  Well done!

Well let's just start with it one of the last great steak houses left in Wisconsin after corporations destroyed proper dining.  Then I'll go ahead and offer the fact of they can actually make a proper old fashioned.  But the most desirable part of this location would rest with the fact that the employees are well educated on what they are actually serving and treat the customers with a proper level of decency, and my bartender had a really awesome napkin flip trip while serving.  Mostly I would say that the atmosphere is deserving of what a proper northern steak house should have, and I would highly recommend to my friends and family.

It was my first time having a steak, of any sort, and now I set an incredibly high bar. The establishment was busy, however the waiter was doing his best to keep us appraised of the dish situation. 

For a birthday dinner, it was definitely a night to enjoy. The chocolate cake was delicious too!

Excellent example of the Wisconsin tavern culture. Sunday all day happy hour delivers $4.25 half liters of good German beer in one bar on the premises. There are two other bars and a restaurant as well as a hotel in the same property.

The food, service and entertainment were great. I normally do not frequent this type of restaurant,  but I must say I will definitely go again. I can't even tell you what I ordered. I let the server surprise me. It was great. Oh no, I hope I get the same server next time!

Beer boots or bust!! Get a boot and share it with friends and abide by the Boot Game rules, conveniently placed on a card on the table. Good German food! Great polka band and dancing!  Steve Meisner is the best band they have- check him out sometime!

Look forward to every chance to return for the wonderful food and drink, but the place needs a bit of a cleaning and more consistent top-notch service to merit top ranking. They can do better. Hope they find the reinvigoration they need.

This is a really cool place. I got some pork schnitzel which was really good. The beer was really good and well priced. The atmosphere was really fun. Everyone seemed to be having a good time. There was a live polka band which was cool but they were a little loud.

Went on the day of a fundraiser, super packed. Met with kindness and good service. Fun times. 
Who doesn't love a plaza burger?

Best burger in town. My family which has been coming for over 2 decades always orders the sauce on the side. You can dip as you please. Wonderful secret sauce! Fries are good too and so is service!!!!

Great place to have a drink and play some games. I don't understand the significance or popularity of the Plaza Burger. It wasn't that special to me, just a burger slathered in 1000 Island dressing. It's so popular that the Monte Carlo in Minneapolis has it as well. 

Still a great bar though.

This was always a back-up plan when I used to do the college bar scene. Now I get lunch there and enjoy probably the best hidden Burger Spot in Madison. Order the plaza burger with cheese and dip it in a little ketchup. Probably the best Secret in Madison.

Paid with $100. Was given counterfeit change. Called and reported the problem. Manager seemed indifferent. Willl not be returning. Will report to FBI fraud and Madison police since manager of bar couldn't be bothered and showed little interest. Beware of this bar!! Definitely a scam going on behind the bar.
